{"editorCode":"      ;Ratio height/hypotenuses\n\n;Oscar wrote the procedure \"height\" in order to construct the height that corresponds to the hypotenuses of a right triangle. The only things he knows is the length of the two perpendicular sides :x and :y and the measure of its angles.\n;Run the procedure \"height\" and check if Oscar achieved his goal. \n\n;----------------        -------------\n\nTO height :h :x :y :c1 :t \nbk :h lt 90 fd :c1\npu bk :c1  pd \nbk :y*cos(:t) rt :t fd :y lt 90 fd :x\nlt 90+:t fd :c1\nend \n\nclean\nheight 40 100 200 85 20 \n\n\n\n\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"\t\t     RATIO HEIGHT/HYPOTENUSES\n\t\t   \n      **************************************\nTask\n.............................\t\t\n1.  Define and run the procedure \"height 40 100 200 85 20\". Enable the sliders of the variation tool (by clicking on the trace of the avatar) and investigate the role of the variables :h, :x, :y, :c1 and :t. \n\nUsing the variation tool, try to locate the following parts of the triangle:\nhypotenuses, perpendicular sides and height.\n\n  Then try to \"close\" the right triangle by using the sliders of the variables.\n\n   •    On which variables does the \"closing\" depend on?\n\n  Compose a conjecture and then test it.  \n  Replace the variable :c1 with the right elements.\n\n2. What do you notice?\n\n   •    Did Oscar reach his goal?\n   •    Does the avatar construct the height towards the hypotenuses correctly? \n\n If not, help Oscar fix the problem in the procedure. \n\n\n\t\t\t\t---------------\n\t\t\t\t  TIPS\n\t\t\t\t--------------\n* You can change the value range for each variable. This will help your exploration. \n * In case you want to use the sine or the cosine of an angle :t, you can use the commands sin(:t) or cos(:t). \n   •    What is the relation between the two acute angles of a right triangle?\n\n\n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}